<apex:page sideBar="true">
    <apex:styleSheet value="{!URLFOR($Resource.AboutServicesProjectManager, 'inc/css/AboutServicesProjectManager.css')}"/>
     
    <h1 id="header">Services Project Manager</h1>
    <div id="leftContainer">
        <p class="paragraph">Services Project Manager for AppExchange eliminates the need for services organizations to manage 
        complex projects by juggling multiple spreadsheets. It consolidates services management to provide an easy way to track 
        and monitor your engagements. You can allocate consultant time based on the skills of each consultant and manage engagements 
        you’ve assigned to partners.</p>
        <p class="paragraph">In addition, Services Project Manager provides a consolidated way for your team to submit and review time
        and expense reports. You spend less time rounding up information and create reports that are more reliable. The application lets 
        you manage your organization’s activities using your own services methodology and knowledge management database.</p>
        
        <fieldset> 
            <legend>Additional Help and Training</legend>
            <ul>
                <li>To learn more about using this application in your environment, contact your Salesforce administrator.</li>
                <li>For answers to questions about using Salesforce, subscribers can contact customer support by clicking the Help &amp; 
                Training link within the Salesforce application</li>
            </ul> 
        </fieldset>     
     </div>

     <div id="rightContainer">  
        <h2 class="subTitlle">The AppExchange</h2>
        <p class="paragraph">The AppExchange is the world’s first on-demand application-sharing service. 
        The dozens of pre-built applications and components it offers have been created by salesforce.com 
        customers, developers, and partners. With these apps, users can do everything from managing expenses 
        to tracking purchasing to monitoring recruiting. Companies can browse, test drive, and install these 
        apps into their salesforce.com accounts with a single click.</p>
        <p class="paragraph">Using the AppExchange, organizations can easily add new apps to their current salesforce.com 
        deployments, run them alongside their existing on-demand applications, and easily customize them 
        to meet their unique needs. The breadth of applications on the AppExchange — including CRM and 
        many other types of business apps — is limited only by the imagination of its publishers and the 
        on-demand community itself.</p> 
        
     </div>

</apex:page>